Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the #oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once the oil is hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}, then transfer to a #bowl and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl and whisk. Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into another #bowl and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Season the @British chicken thighs{3} with salt and pepper, then dip it into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Return the #frying pan{} to high heat with enough @olive oil{for frying} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for ~{2-3%minutes} before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay in the chicken. Reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{10-14%minutes} total. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust the heat if necessary.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate lined with kitchen paper.

== Buffalo Sauce ==

In a #medium saucepan{}, add the @water{1%tbsp} and two thirds of the @cider vinegar{30%ml}. Place the pan on medium-high heat and bring to a boil. Simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @sriracha sauce{45%ml} and @honey{30%ml} until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 minute.

Mix in the @butter{20%g} until melted, then stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g}. Leave to cool in the pan until ready to serve.

== Baby Leaf Salad ==

Meanwhile, chop the @medium tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

In a large #bowl, add the remaining @cider vinegar{15%ml} and the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Toss in the tomatoes to dress them.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the bowl and toss to coat.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, thinly slice your crispy chicken thighs.

Share your fries between your plates, then top with the crispy chicken and drizzle over the buffalo inspired sauce. Sprinkle with the bacon and @crumbled blue cheese{30%g} - as much as you'd like.

Serve with the baby leaf salad alongside. Enjoy!